  "2026-07-03T15:21:04.554Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: focused changed specs passed (2 files/18 tests); expanded touched suite passed (14 files/409 tests); pnpm typecheck, pnpm contracts:check, pnpm security:scan, pnpm audit --audit-level moderate, git diff --check, and pnpm lint all passed after pruning one stale ESLint complexity suppression. Full coverage passed 263 files / 5311 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines. Manual temp dist CLI smoke passed at /tmp/tmp.sa15A2d7KS covering init, bundled kanban install/profile dry-run, create/files/test/search/close/health."
  "2026-07-03T15:34:34.340Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence update after dependency refresh: updated compatible dev toolchain deps tsx 4.23.0 and eslint-plugin-unicorn 70.0.0; left @types/node on 22.20.0 because the repo runtime contract remains Node >=22.18 and pnpm wanted stays 22.20.0. Gates after refresh: focused specs passed (2 files/18 tests), pnpm typecheck passed, pnpm contracts:check passed, pnpm lint passed with ESLint clean + jscpd 0 clones + static quality gate, pnpm security:scan found no credential-like secrets, pnpm audit --audit-level moderate found no known vulnerabilities, git diff --check passed, and full coverage passed 263 files / 5311 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines. Manual temp dist CLI smoke passed at /tmp/tmp.eaYBDgtes6 covering init, bundled kanban install, profile list/apply dry-run, create, files, linked test run, search, close, and health. GitHub live checks: no open issues or PRs; code-scanning/secret-scanning/dependabot alert APIs returned 404 unavailable to this token/repo, so not counted as clean alerts. Auto-release live checks: 2026-07-03 scheduled auto-release succeeded on main, GitHub release v2026.7.3 exists, npm reports @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.3, and release environment secrets NPM_TOKEN/RELEASE_PAT/SENTRY tokens are present. Observability: sentry-telemetry gate passed with Sentry critical=0/high=0 over 14 days and telemetry finish error rate 0.67% with 0 missing-error-code rows; direct sentry-cli list succeeded when pointed at SENTRY_PERSONAL_ADMIN_TOKEN."
  "2026-07-03T15:36:17.009Z",claude-code-agent,"Changelog evidence: pnpm changelog:pm regenerated CHANGELOG.md with Unreleased entries for pm-7wmq and pm-4i73 using pm-changelog 2026.6.30; pnpm changelog:pm:check then passed unchanged. Timestamp-only .agents/pm/extensions/.managed-extensions.json churn from reinstall was intentionally excluded from the commit."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-03T14:54:32.882Z",maintainer-agent,"Audit findings (4 parallel reviews, worst first):\n1. release-automation-contract.spec.ts — 4 tests assert exact SOURCE SUBSTRINGS of scripts (bundle-cli lock internals, telemetry gate literals, Sentry query signature, release-notes date lines) instead of behavior; brittle to refactors, blind to semantic regressions.\n2. ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts:75-220 — ~90-line verbatim mirror of ci.yml (step names, full cache keys byte-for-byte); change-detector, not a contract. Keep: SHA-pin regexes, no-publish negative checks, 120-file cap.\n3. cli-main-errors.spec.ts:281-284 — setRecoveredExtensionServices tested with bare not.toThrow(); a no-op body would pass. Effect observable via runActiveServiceOverrideSync.\n4. stats-command.spec.ts:303-323 — title claims tag-prefix filtering is tested; only 4x toBeDefined, prefix never asserted.\n5. restore-command.spec.ts:546/561/576 — rollback tests use rejects.toBeTruthy(); early NOT_FOUND rejection makes rollback assertions vacuous.\n6. Over-mocked thin specs: invalidate-search-caches.spec.ts (condition AND effect mocked), list-sort-branches.spec.ts (whole store virtualized), search-command.spec.ts on-read-hook block (asserts only against mocked extensions module).\n7. Scattered: rejects.toBeDefined() where ENOENT/EACCES should be pinned (telemetry-consent, item-format-migration, search-cache, telemetry-runtime, cli.integration, todos-extension); register-commands else-path block with 1 bare toHaveBeenCalled for 12 dispatches; smoke-cleanup mock-fs not.toThrow-only; package-manifest regex-parses source instead of importing.\nCleared: no tautological mock-asserting-mock anywhere; 82 specs use real temp FS; integration layer (31 specs, zero vi.mock) runs the built CLI with exit-code/stdout/FS assertions; ~80% of toBeDefined hits are TS narrowing followed by real assertions; coverage pragmas (498) all justified defensive/unreachable with budget frozen.\nRemediation running as 4 parallel fix agents with disjoint file ownership; gates to re-verify after: coverage 100x4, eslint 0 warnings, jscpd 0 clones."
learnings[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-03T14:54:50.691Z",maintainer-agent,"Contract-spec antipattern: asserting exact source substrings (toContain on implementation code/YAML) mirrors the implementation instead of pinning behavior — passes rename-blind on real regressions, breaks on harmless refactors, and trains copy-paste test edits. Convert to executed-behavior tests (run script with --json + fixtures) or parsed-structure invariants (YAML job/matrix/SHA-pin checks)."
  "2026-07-03T14:54:51.152Z",maintainer-agent,"Grep counts of toBeDefined()/not.toThrow() overstate hollowness ~5x: in this suite ~80% were TypeScript narrowing guards immediately followed by exact assertions, or legitimate accept-path contracts paired with exact-message throw tests. Judge each hit against the source under test before flagging."
  "2026-07-03T14:54:51.764Z",maintainer-agent,"100%-coverage gates breed two artifacts to watch for: (1) coverage-marking test blocks that invoke many branches with a single bare toHaveBeenCalled(), and (2) _testOnly seams testing runtime-unreachable defensive branches. Fix (1) by pinning per-call args; (2) is acceptable when the branch is a real drift guard, since the pragma budget (498, burn-down-only) forbids new ignore pragmas."
  "2026-07-03T14:54:52.329Z",maintainer-agent,"Mock-audit rubric that worked: classify every vi.mock as boundary (child_process/fetch/TTY/SDK/clock = fine), first-party-replacement (suspect: test passes with broken impl), or mock-asserting-mock (tautological). House style of withTempPmPath real-FS workspaces plus fake-transport-at-the-boundary (e.g. fake git writing real trees) is why this suite audited clean."
  "2026-07-03T14:54:52.911Z",maintainer-agent,"rejects.toBeDefined()/toBeTruthy() on fs promises is a vacuous-pass hazard: any rejection (typo'd path, EACCES, early usage error) satisfies it. Pin rejects.toMatchObject({ code: \"ENOENT\" | \"EACCES\" }) — and for rollback tests, pin the error to the induced failure point so an early rejection can't fake a successful rollback."
